  "text": "HTTP filter chains in Envoy are registered through a multi-stage process involving proto configuration, factory registration, and runtime execution. The HttpConnectionManager proto (envoyproxy/data-plane-api at envoy/extensions/filters/network/http_connection_manager/v3/http_connection_manager.proto and mirrored in envoyproxy/envoy at api/envoy/extensions/filters/network/http_connection_manager/v3/http_connection_manager.proto) defines the `http_filters` field as a repeated HttpFilter message that specifies the filter configuration schema.\n\nThe FilterChainFactory interface (envoyproxy/envoy at envoy/http/filter_factory.h, lines 89-119) defines two pure virtual methods: `createFilterChain()` which creates the filter chain for new HTTP streams, and `createUpgradeFilterChain()` for handling protocol upgrades like WebSocket. This interface is implemented by HttpConnectionManagerConfig (envoyproxy/envoy at source/extensions/filters/network/http_connection_manager/config.h, lines 127-129).\n\nDuring configuration initialization (HttpConnectionManagerConfig constructor at envoyproxy/envoy source/extensions/filters/network/http_connection_manager/config.cc, line 346), the FilterChainHelper template class (envoyproxy/envoy source/common/http/filter_chain_helper.h, lines 69-201) processes the http_filters configuration. The FilterChainHelper::processFilters method (lines 87-102) iterates through each filter in the proto config, instantiates filter factories via the plugin registry, and builds a list of FilterFactoriesList. This list is stored in the HttpConnectionManagerConfig's filter_factories_ member.\n\nAt runtime, when a new HTTP stream is created, the FilterManager (envoyproxy/envoy source/common/http/filter_manager.h, lines 638-640) is instantiated and its createFilterChain() method is called (source/common/http/filter_manager.cc, lines 1550-1586). FilterManager implements the FilterChainManager interface. The createFilterChain() method calls the FilterChainFactory's createFilterChain() method, which delegates to HttpConnectionManagerConfig::createFilterChain() (source/extensions/filters/network/http_connection_manager/config.cc, lines 780-784).\n\nHttpConnectionManagerConfig::createFilterChain() then invokes FilterChainUtility::createFilterChainForFactories() (source/common/http/filter_chain_helper.cc, lines 17-47), which iterates through the pre-computed filter factories and calls FilterManager::applyFilterFactoryCb() for each filter. This method (FilterManager in filter_manager.h, line 697) creates an instance of each filter by calling the stored filter factory callback (FilterFactoryCb) with a reference to FilterChainFactoryCallbacks (envoyproxy/envoy envoy/http/filter.h, lines 1224-1257). The FilterChainFactoryCallbacks interface provides methods like addStreamDecoderFilter(), addStreamEncoderFilter(), and addStreamFilter() that allow the filter factories to add their filter instances to the filter chain.\n\nThe actual filter execution happens through the FilterManager's decoder and encoder filter chains. ActiveStreamFilterBase (envoyproxy/envoy source/common/http/filter_manager.h, lines 65-237) provides the base class for managing filter iteration state and handling filter callbacks. The commonContinue() method (source/common/http/filter_manager.cc, lines 52-113) drives the filter chain execution, calling doHeaders(), doData(), and doTrailers() methods that iterate through the filters in order.\n\nThe complete registration and execution chain flows as follows: (1) Proto configuration defines filter_chains in HttpConnectionManager, (2) HttpConnectionManagerConfig processes this configuration using FilterChainHelper during construction, (3) FilterChainHelper instantiates filter factories from the registry and stores them in FilterFactoriesList, (4) At runtime, FilterManager::createFilterChain() is called for each new stream, (5) HttpConnectionManagerConfig::createFilterChain() delegates to FilterChainUtility::createFilterChainForFactories(), (6) For each stored filter factory, FilterManager::applyFilterFactoryCb() calls the factory callback with FilterChainFactoryCallbacks, (7) The filter callbacks add the filter instances to the decoder/encoder filter chains, (8) ActiveStreamFilterBase::commonContinue() iterates through the filters in response to stream events."
}

